item.description: Got my beater car to get me through school, and on the drive home from passing my masters defense, the car died. In a weird spot as im thankful for finishing school and having a good thanksgiving with family, but my future prospects are now bleak. Edit: Thank you for the kind words! To answer a few questions, the transmission gave up the ghost and won't go out of first gear anymore. I live in Texas, and the degree is in Computer Science. I'm usually a code monkey, but honestly looking for anything that can pay the bills at this point.

item.title: FLOATING HEAD MAKEUP - MCROFT07
item.description: btw, I usually post like 1% of the videos on imgur that I post on socials because I don't want to spam. Essentially I just post my favourites. If you'd like to see my other videos please follow me elsewhere. This makeup look I believe was originally created by Victoria Whitlow in 2016. I've seen a bunch of people recreate it and it has angered me beyond compare that they haven't credited the original artist even thought she doesn't create anymore so I thought I'll call it out in the video. Anyway, it's a cool illusion!! Ponder: wouldn't the world be so much more beautiful if we appreciated artists during their lifetime instead of after they've passed away. EDIT: afaik Victoria Whitlow is not dead, it was just food for thought I'm posting less because some of the comments made me really uncomfortable. Not sure if I will read the comments for a bit. If you see people being weird please downvote or report them because they're the exact people that make women feel unsafe.
